# Selective Test Running

- During an implementation plan, run the smallest checks that directly cover the code changed in the task just completed.
- Prefer targeted unit tests, individual test files or filters, crate-specific tests, package-specific tests, and focused lint/type checks while iterating.
- Do not run workspace-wide or otherwise full test suites between plan tasks unless the user explicitly requests it or targeted checks would be misleading.
- Run full test suites only once, at the very end of the plan, after all targeted checks are clean.
